<subSubSection lastPageId="23" lastPageNumber="24" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1436,1866,2026]" lastBlockId="23.[151,1436,152,588]" lastPageId="23" lastPageNumber="24" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,383,1962,1988]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Diagnosis of male.</emphasis>
This species has a deeply excised tridentate mandible that has a complete dorsal carina and a vertical apex (
<figureCitation box="[391,480,2000,2026]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 24" captionStartId="12.[151,275,1917,1941]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,381,1880]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[151,1436,381,1896]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 24. Head, anterior view; except ventral view 17. 13. Odontophotopsis serca; 14. O. setifera; 15. Sphaeropthalma. amphion; 16. S. angulifera; 17. S. angulifera; 18. S. arota; 19. S. becki; 20. S. blakeii; 21. S. difficilis; 22. S. ferruginea; 23. S. ignacio; and 24. S. macswaini." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/196849/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
Fig. 
<number box="[447,480,2000,2026]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="22.0">22</number>
</figureCitation>
), has sternal felt lines that are mere tufts, lacks mesosternal and coxal processes, and the genitalia have a clavate cuspis that has bifid-tipped setae located ventrally towards the apex (
<figureCitation box="[1328,1415,152,178]" captionStart="FIGURES 49 – 58" captionStartId="18.[151,270,1727,1751]" captionTargetBox="[156,1435,303,1676]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[151,1436,293,1706]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 49 – 58. Acanthophotopsis falciformis: 49. Genitalia, lateral view (from Tanner &amp; Pitts 2009). Dilophotopsis paron: 50. Genitalia, ventral, dorsal, inner lateral view, and lateral view of penis valve; and 51. Mesosoma, oblique ventral view (from Wilson &amp; Pitts 2008). Sphaeropthalma amphion: 52. Genitalia, dorsal, inner lateral view, and lateral view of penis valve (from Pitts et al. 2004). Sphaeropthalma angulifera: 53. Genitalia, dorsal, inner lateral view, and lateral view of penis valve (from Wilson &amp; Pitts 2009). Mandible, anterior view: 54. Sphaeropthalma angulifera; and 55. Sphaeropthalma mendica (from Wilson &amp; Pitts 2009). Sphaeropthalma ferruginea: 56. Genitalia, ventral view left, dorsal view right. Sphaeropthalma ignacio: 57. Genitalia, ventral view left, dorsal view right. Sphaeropthalma macswaini: 56. Genitalia, inner lateral view left." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/196854/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
Fig. 
<number box="[1382,1415,152,178]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" value="56.0">56</number>
</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis box="[151,247,189,214]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Female.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
